│ My analysis indicates that the crash is due to an incomplete │
│ implementation in `canonicalizeICmpBool` within              │
│ `InstCombineCompares.cpp`. This function is designed to      │
│ simplify `i1` (boolean) comparisons but fails to handle all  │
│ predicates when one operand is a constant `true` or `false`, │
│ specifically for vector types.                               │
│                                                              │
│ The reproducer demonstrates a crash with `icmp ne <vector of │
│ i1> %X, zeroinitializer`. The existing logic in              │
│ `canonicalizeICmpBool` for a `zeroinitializer` operand only  │
│ handles `ICMP_EQ`, `ICMP_ULE`, and `ICMP_SGE`, causing any   │
│ other predicate to hit an `unreachable` statement.           │
│                                                              │
│ The fix is to expand the logic in `canonicalizeICmpBool` to  │
│ correctly handle all applicable predicates for comparisons   │
│ against `zero` and `one`. For `icmp ne %X, false`, the       │
│ result is simply `%X`. For other predicates, the comparison  │
│ can be simplified to a constant `true` or `false` vector.    │
│                                                              │
│ I will now apply the necessary changes to                    │
│ `canonicalizeICmpBool`.                                      │
